d%20social%20media%20use%20in%20adolescence%20is%20linked%20to%20paranoia%2C%20delusions%2C%20hallucinations%20and%20'bizarre%20ideas'%20by%20the%20time%20a%20person%20reaches%2023.%20The%20study%2C%20based%20on%20the%20analysis%20of%20the%20data%20of%201%2C226%20participants%20born%20between%201997%20and%201998%2C%20has%20been%20published%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1001%2Fjamapsychiatry.2024.0384%5C%22%3Ejournal%20%3Cem%3EJAMA%20Psychiatry%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTrajectories%20of%20higher%20video%20gaming%20and%20increasing-then-decreasing%20(curved)%20computer%20use%20during%20adolescence%20were%20associated%20with%20higher%20levels%20of%20psychotic%20experiences%20at%20age%2023%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20-%20from%20McGill%20University%20in%20Canada%20-%20wrote%20in%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20research%2C%20participants%20were%20asked%20questions%20to%20determine%20if%20they%20had%20experienced%20periods%20of%20persecutory%20ideations%2C%20bizarre%20experiences%2C%20and%20perceptual%20abnormalities.%20Some%20of%20these%20questions%20were%3A%20%26quot%3BHave%20you%20ever%20felt%20as%20if%20people%20seem%20to%20drop%20hints%20about%20you%20or%20say%20things%20with%20a%20double%20meaning%3F%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3BHave%20you%20ever%20felt%20as%20if%20the%20thoughts%20in%20your%20head%20are%20not%20your%20own%3F%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BHave%20you%20ever%20heard%20voices%20when%20you%20are%20alone%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnalysing%20the%20responses%2C%20the%20researchers%20reached%20to%20the%20conclusion%20that%20playing%20video%20games%20more%20during%20adolescence%20was%20associated%20with%203-7%20per%20cent%20more%20psychotic%20experiences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20researchers%20said%20the%20technology%20itself%20is%20not%20to%20be%20blamed%2C%20adding%20that%20a%20child's%20addiction%20to%20the%20devices%20could%20be%20a%20warning%20that%20they%20are%20already%20vulnerable%20to%20mental%20illness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHigher%20media%20use%20and%20mental%20health%20problems%20appear%20to%20share%20risk%20factors%2C%20such%20as%20parental%20mental%20health%20problems%2C%20loneliness%2C%20bullying%20and%20parent-child%20relational%20problems%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20team%20said%20in%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20research%20team%20also%20said%20that%20abruptly%20depriving%20the%20youngsters%20of%20screen%20time%20may%20not%20help%20and%20could%20be%20more%20harmful.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20hope%20that%20the%20study%20will%20help%20psychologists%20understand%20why%20teenagers%20may%20develop%20psychotic%20experiences%20and%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20best%20help%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712831820000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2Fv0o9ouio_video-game-unsplash_625x300_11_April_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fchildren-addicted-to-video-games-smartphones-at-risk-of-psychosis-study-5419427%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22However%2C%20researchers%20said%20the%20technology%20itself%20is%20not%20to%20be%20blamed%2C%20adding%20that%20a%20child's%20addiction%20to%20the%20devices%20could%20be%20a%20warning%20that%20they%20are%20already%20vulnerable%20to%20mental%20illness.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fchildren-addicted-to-video-games-smartphones-at-risk-of-psychosis-study-5419427%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fchildren-addicted-to-video-games-smartphones-at-risk-of-psychosis-study-5419427%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fchildren-addicted-to-video-games-smartphones-at-risk-of-psychosis-study-5419427%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22My%203-year-old%20son%20drowned%20in%20a%20backyard%20pool.%20I%20wish%20I'd%20known%20these%207%20swim%20safety%20tips.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222975%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chezik%20Tsunoda's%20three-year-old%20son%2C%20Yori%2C%20wearing%20a%20grey%20shirt%20and%20blue%20glasses.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6615a7c416bde8d4ead7204f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222231%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChezik%20Tsunoda%20founded%20the%20nonprofit%20No%20More%20Under%20after%20her%20son%2C%20Yori%2C%20drowned.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20Chezik%20Tsunoda%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EChezik%20Tsunoda's%20three-year-old%2C%20Yori%2C%20died%20after%20swimming%20in%20a%20friend's%20pool.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETsunoda%20founded%20No%20More%20Under%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20dedicated%20to%20swim%20safety.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20says%20all%20parents%20should%20appoint%20a%20%26quot%3Bwater%20watcher%26quot%3B%20and%20learn%20CPR.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nomoreunder.org%2Fwho-we-are%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EChezik%20Tsunoda%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20September%202018%2C%20I%20had%20four%20boys%20under%20the%20age%20of%20seven.%20Life%20was%20full%20of%20appointments%20for%20the%20boys%2C%20preschool%20drop-offs%2C%20park%20visits%20to%20get%20their%20energy%20out%2C%20and%20making%20sure%20everyone%20was%20fed%20on%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20juggle%2C%20so%20I%20was%20looking%20forward%20to%20an%20afternoon%20at%20our%20friend's%20house%20near%20our%20home%20in%20Washington%20state.%20They%20had%20a%20pool%20and%20kids%20of%20similar%20ages.%20The%20dads%20were%20swimming%20with%20the%20children%2C%20while%20I%20played%20with%20the%20two%20babies.%20The%20other%20mom%20was%20in%20the%20kitchen%20prepping%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20one%20point%2C%20I%20looked%20at%20my%20then-husband%20and%20asked%2C%20%26quot%3BWhere's%20Yori%3F%26quot%3B%20I%20hadn't%20seen%20our%20three-year-old%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20follow%20up%20on%20my%20instinct.%20A%20few%20minutes%20later%2C%20my%20oldest%20son%2C%20who%20was%20six%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BYori's%20winning%20the%20contest%20for%20holding%20his%20breath%20the%20longest.%26quot%3B%20With%20those%20words%2C%20our%20lives%20turned%20upside%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMy%20son%20was%20on%20life%20support%20for%20two%20weeks%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20friend%20gave%20Yori%20CPR%2C%20and%20then%20I%20stepped%20in.%20When%20paramedics%20arrived%2C%20they%20were%20able%20to%20restart%20his%20heart%2C%20and%20for%20two%20weeks%2C%20I%20clung%20on%20to%20hope%20%E2%80%94%20any%20hope%20%E2%80%94%20that%20my%20boy%20would%20open%20his%20eyes.%20He%20never%20did.%20Finally%2C%20we%20made%20the%20decision%20to%20take%20him%20off%20life%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20those%20first%20days%20home%20without%20Yori%2C%20I%20dove%20into%20research%20as%20soon%20as%20I%20put%20my%20youngest%20to%20sleep.%20I%20wondered%20if%20there%20was%20anything%20I%20could%20have%20done%20differently.%20I%20learned%20that%20drowning%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fdrowning%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eleading%20cause%20of%20death%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20children%20ages%20one%20through%20four.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20six%20years%20later%2C%20I%20understand%20the%20impact.%20There%20are%20families%20like%20ours%2C%20who%20have%20lost%20a%20child%2C%20and%20others%20who%20have%20a%20child%20with%20permanent%20brain%20damage%20or%20other%20long-term%20disabilities%20from%20drowning%20incidents.%20For%20every%20fatal%20accident%2C%20there%20are%20seven%20emergency%20room%20visits%20related%20to%20downing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrowning%20can%20happen%20to%20anyone%2C%20but%20it%20impacts%20certain%20demographics%20more.%20Black%20children%20like%20Yori%20are%20more%20than%202.5%20times%20more%20likely%20than%20their%20white%20peers%20to%20drown.%20It%20makes%20sense%20%E2%80%94%20my%20grandmothers%20weren't%20allowed%20to%20swim%20in%20public%20pools%2C%20so%20it's%20little%20wonder%20their%20great-grandchildren%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20be%20comfortable%20around%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chezik%20Tsunoda%20with%20her%20three%20sons%2C%20smiling%20and%20staring%20at%20the%20camera%2C%20while%20outdoors%20on%20a%20sunny%20day.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6615a4da16bde8d4ead71a25%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222689%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChezik%20Tsunoda%20still%20allows%20her%20three%20living%20sons%20to%20swim%2C%20but%20has%20taught%20them%20water%20safety.%3Cp%3EPhoto%20Credit%3A%20Tim%20Gbunblee%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20founded%20a%20nonprofit%20to%20educate%20others%20about%20water%20safety%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20four%20sons%2C%20but%20only%20three%20are%20alive.%20I%20use%20the%20time%20that%20I%20should%20be%20caring%20for%20Yori%20%E2%80%94%20feeding%20him%2C%20going%20to%20parent-teacher%20conferences%2C%20and%20tucking%20him%20in%20%E2%80%94%20to%20educate%20others%20about%20swim%20safety.%20I%20founded%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nomoreunder.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENo%20More%20Under%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20that%20aims%20to%20prevent%20drownings%20by%20increasing%20equitable%20access%20to%20swimming%20lessons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20come%20into%20the%20summer%20season%2C%20with%20its%20beach%20days%20and%20pool%20parties%2C%20I%20want%20parents%20to%20see%20through%20the%20false%20sense%20of%20security%20we%20have%20around%20water.%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20cause%20fear%2C%20but%20it's%20important%20that%20we%20recognize%20the%20dangers%20that%20come%20with%20water%20play%20and%20make%20sure%20our%20behaviors%20reflect%20those%20dangers.%20Here's%20how%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EAppoint%20a%20water%20watcher%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20day%20in%20the%20pool%2C%20I%20trusted%20that%20the%20dads%20were%20watching%20Yori.%20But%20we%20hadn't%20formally%20appointed%20anyone%20to%20watch%20the%20children.%20Now%2C%20I%20tell%20families%20to%20designate%20a%20water%20watcher%20%E2%80%94%20someone%20whose%20entire%20job%20is%20to%20have%20their%20eyes%20on%20kids%20in%20the%20pool%20(not%20on%20a%20book%2C%20phone%2C%20or%20friend%20who%20you're%20chatting%20with).%20Consider%20having%20a%20badge%20or%20other%20identifying%20item%20so%20there's%20no%20confusion%20about%20who%20is%20on%20duty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3ETeach%20kids%20to%20respect%20the%20water%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20teach%20our%20children%20the%20dangers%20of%20roads%20or%20strangers%2C%20and%20we%20need%20to%20instill%20the%20same%20respect%20for%20water.%20I%20never%20want%20children%20to%20be%20afraid%20of%20water%2C%20but%20I%20want%20them%20to%20know%20it%20can%20be%20dangerous%2C%20and%20that%20they%20should%20take%20precautions.%20Tell%20little%20ones%20to%20never%20get%20in%20the%20water%20%E2%80%94%20even%20the%20bath%20%E2%80%94%20without%20telling%20an%20adult.%20Remind%20older%20children%20to%20never%2C%20ever%20swim%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EReach%2C%20throw%2C%20don't%20go%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20all%20know%20stop%2C%20drop%2C%20and%20roll%2C%20but%20you're%20more%20likely%20to%20experience%20a%20drowning%20event%20than%20a%20fire.%20That's%20why%20I%20use%20the%20phrase%2C%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ymcapkc.org%2Fblog%2Fwater-safety-reach-throw-dont-go%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereach%2C%20throw%2C%20don't%20go%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20When%20someone%20is%20drowning%2C%20reach%20toward%20them%2C%20throw%20them%20a%20flotation%20device%2C%20but%20%E2%80%94%20unless%20it's%20a%20very%20small%20child%20%E2%80%94%20don't%20go%20to%20them.%20A%20drowning%20person%20is%20panicking%20and%20can%20easily%20bring%20you%20under%2C%20too.%20Teach%20your%20kids%20to%20reach%2C%20throw%2C%20don't%20go.%20Then%2C%20practice%20the%20steps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EStick%20with%20swim%20lessons%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20weeks%20before%20Yori%20drowned%2C%20he%20tried%20swimming%20lessons%20and%20hated%20them.%20So%2C%20like%20lots%20of%20parents%2C%20I%20didn't%20push%20it.%20I%20figured%20we%20had%20time.%20I'll%20always%20wonder%20if%20lessons%20would%20have%20made%20a%20difference.%20Find%20a%20qualified%20instructor%20who%20can%20help%20your%20child%20feel%20comfortable%20and%20safe%20in%20the%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EUse%20life%20jackets%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20day%20Yori%20died%2C%20I%20had%20pulled%20back%20into%20our%20driveway%20to%20get%20his%20life%20jacket.%20But%20he%20wasn't%20wearing%20it%20when%20he%20drowned.%20Keep%20flotation%20devices%20on%20even%20when%20kids%20aren't%20actively%20in%20the%20water%2C%20and%20use%20them%20until%20your%20child%20is%20a%20very%20confident%20swimmer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3ELearn%20CPR%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EI%20still%20question%20whether%20I%20did%20CPR%20right%20on%20Yori.%20I%20urge%20every%20parent%20or%20caregiver%20to%20learn%20CPR%2C%20because%20it%20could%20save%20a%20child's%20life%20this%20summer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EKnow%20where%20you're%20swimming%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EI%20knew%20how%20to%20get%20to%20my%20friend's%20house%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20know%20her%20address%20to%20give%20to%20911.%20Always%20know%20the%20address%20where%20you%20are%2C%20whether%20it's%20a%20friend's%20house%20or%20a%20public%20beach.%20Remember%2C%20every%20second%20counts%20for%20first%20responders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20summer%2C%20my%20three%20living%20sons%20will%20enjoy%20pools%20and%20beaches.%20I'll%20do%20my%20best%20to%20share%20their%20joy%2C%20despite%20my%20trauma%2C%20but%20I'll%20be%20doing%20it%20with%20an%20awareness%20and%20caution%20I%20wish%20I'd%20had%20six%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%