20with%20mercenary%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gadgets360.com%2Ftags%2Fspyware%5C%22%3Espyware%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CApple%20detected%20that%20you%20are%20being%20targeted%20by%20a%20mercenary%20spyware%20attack%20that%20is%20trying%20to%20remotely%20compromise%20the%20iPhone%20associated%20with%20your%20Apple%20ID%20-xxx-%2C%E2%80%9D%C2%A0the%20company%20says%20in%20the%20email%20sent%20out%20to%20users%20on%20April%2010%20at%2012pm%20PT%20(12%3A30am%20IST%20on%20Thursday)%20viewed%20by%20Gadgets%20360.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20email%20informs%20users%20asks%20users%20to%20take%20the%20warning%20seriously%2C%20adding%20that%20that%20Apple%20has%20%26quot%3Bhigh%20confidence%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20warning%20%E2%80%94%20even%20though%20it%20is%20never%20possible%20to%20achieve%20absolute%20certainty%20when%20detecting%20such%20attacks.%20Apple's%20email%20also%20states%20that%20it%20has%20notified%20users%20in%20150%20countries%20to%20date%2C%20and%20the%20company%20does%20not%20attribute%20these%20targeted%20spyware%20attacks%20%E2%80%94%20including%20those%20using%20software%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gadgets360.com%2Ftags%2Fpegasus%5C%22%3EPegasus%3C%2Fa%3E%20developed%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gadgets360.com%2Ftags%2Fnso-group%5C%22%3ENSO%20Group%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20to%20specific%20attackers%20or%20geographic%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApple%20has%20advised%20users%20who%20received%20the%20threat%20notification%20email%20to%20enable%20Lockdown%20Mode%20on%20their%20iPhone%20%E2%80%94%20a%20special%20mode%20that%20reduces%20the%20avenues%20for%20spyware%20attacks%20by%20disabling%20several%20features.%20Users%20are%20also%20advised%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gadgets360.com%2Fmobiles%2Fnews%2Fios-17-4-1-ipados-update-changelog-bug-security-fixes-5288172%5C%22%3Eupdate%20to%20iOS%2017.4.1%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20keep%20other%20devices%2C%20messaging%2C%20and%20cloud%20apps%20updated.%20Users%20t