pularity%20during%20the%20time%20of%20the%20Mughal%20rule.%20In%20fact%2C%20it%20is%20said%20that%20Emperor%20Humayun%20ignited%20the%20love%20for%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eseviyan%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0in%20the%20court%20by%20reintroducing%20the%20Persian%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ekurma%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0as%C2%A0%3Cem%3Edum%20ki%20seviyan.%20%3C%2Fem%3EBut%2C%20it%20was%C2%A0Emperor%20Shah%20Jahan%20who%20was%20instrumental%20in%20the%20dish%20becoming%20its%20current%20version%20with%20spices%2C%20ghee%20and%20dry%20fruits.%20An%20anecdote%20often%20told%20is%20how%20the%20Emperor%20requested%20a%20special%20sunset-coloured%C2%A0%3Cem%3Evarq%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(an%20edible%20foil%20garnishing)%20to%20accompany%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eseviyan%3C%2Fem%3E.%20This%20tradition%20lasted%20until%20the%20time%20of%20Bahadur%20Shah%20Zafar%20who%20would%20prepare%20his%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eseviyan%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0by%20hand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20ingredient%20entered%20India%2C%20it%20was%20local%20palate%20preferences%20that%20gave%20birth%20to%20the%20many%20vermicelli-based%20dishes%20that%20now%20exist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%E2%80%98Oxford%20Companion%20to%20Food%E2%80%99%20by%20Alan%20Davidson%20and%20Tom%20Jaine%2C%20says%20the%20following%20about%20%3Cem%3Eseviyan%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%20The%20Sanskrit%20name%20for%20noodles%20is%20%3Cem%3Esevika%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20may%20derive%20from%20an%20unrecorded%20word%20meaning%20thread%20connected%20with%20the%20root%20%3Cem%3Esiv%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20refers%20to%20sewing.%20%3Cem%3ESev%3C%2Fem%3E%20are%20crisp%20fried%20noodles%20prepared%20from%20%3Cem%3Ebesan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(chickpea)%20flour.%20%3Cem%3ESeviyan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(also%20%3Cem%3Eseviya%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Esivayya%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Eshavayi%3C%2Fem%3E)%20usually%20refers%20to%20a%20sweet%20dish%20of%20vermicelli%20noodles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20637px)%20100vw%2C%20637px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A