th%20to%20North%20and%20East%20to%20West.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20breakfast%20in%20South%20India%20is%20complete%20without%20an%20order%20for%20%3Cem%3Esemiya%20upma%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20dish%20made%20with%20a%20mixture%20of%20vermicelli%20and%20vegetables)%2C%20while%20in%20the%20North%20the%20fuss-free%20%3Cem%3Enamkeen%20seviyan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(savoury%20vermicelli)%20has%20many%20fans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20South%20or%20North%2C%20everyone%20concedes%20that%20there%20is%20no%20rival%20for%20the%20%3Cem%3Eseviyan%20kheer%20%3C%2Fem%3E(a%20vermicelli%20pudding%20made%20with%20%3Cem%3Eghee%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20rice%20vermicelli%20noodles%2C%20milk%2C%20spices%2C%20and%20a%20sweetener).%20And%20that%20brings%20us%20back%20to%20our%20Eid%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHistory%20sprinkled%20with%20a%20dash%20of%20sweetness%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVermicelli%E2%80%99s%20entry%20into%20India%20was%20marked%20by%20every%20region%20putting%20its%20own%20spin%20on%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F281110%2Fmithai-map-of-india-10-lesser-known-indian-sweets-you-must-try-at-least-once%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20the%20dish%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20the%20West%2C%20adding%20saffron%20and%20chopped%20nuts%20to%20the%20vermicelli%20is%20a%20common%20practice%20while%20in%20the%20North%2C%20this%20is%20substituted%20with%20%3Cem%3Ekhoya%3C%2Fem%3E.%20In%20the%20South%2C%20coconut%20milk%20is%20added%20to%20get%20a%20thick%20consistency%20while%20those%20in%20Odisha%20and%20West%20Bengal%20prefer%20adding%20rosewater.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20way%20vermicelli%20is%20cooked%20depends%20upon%20the%20festive%20occasion%20too.%20For%20instance%2C%20during%20Raksha%20Bandhan%2C%20some%20people%20prepare%20%3Cem%3Emeethe%20java%3C%2Fem%3E%20(vermicelli%20pudding).%20The%20%E2%80%9Causpicious%E2%80%9D%20short%20noodles%20used%20in%20the%20dish%20are%20a%20version%20of%20the%20thinner%